    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's actually terrifying to hear. if they're doing this, i bet they're not just watching the data, they're probably trying to see if they can actually influence my mood by changing the lights/temp. like, if they can trigger a specific emotional response, they've basically succeeded in their test. does that sound like a realistic way for them to validate their tech?",
